Add this after you create df and log10_CFU:

model <- aov(log10_CFU ~ Group * Timepoint, data = df)

res <- residuals(model)

Then you can check residual normality:

pdf("residual_diagnostics.pdf")

qqnorm(res)
qqline(res, col = "red")

hist(res, breaks = 20, main = "Histogram of residuals", xlab = "Residuals")

plot(model, which = 1)

dev.off()

And run Shapiro-Wilk:

shapiro_result <- shapiro.test(res)

write.csv(
  data.frame(
    W = shapiro_result$statistic,
    p_value = shapiro_result$p.value
  ),
  "shapiro_residual_normality.csv",
  row.names = FALSE
)

So in your script, put it before the pairwise tests or near the ANOVA section.
